  "texts": [
    "Since our major contribution is a zero-shot approach, in principle we could have used the entire dataset as a test set.",
    "However, we also need a training set for training the supervised baselines and as an example dataset for the few-shot ADL-LLM.",
    "For this reason, we divided each dataset into 30% for the training set and 70% for the testing set.",
    "This splitting reflects a labeled data scarcity scenario, where only a limited labeled dataset is available.",
    "The training set is not used in any way by zero-shot ADL-LLM, while it is used to train the supervised baselines and to generate the pool of examples in few-shot ADL-LLM.In our experiments, the training and test sets contain data from the same user."
  ],
